Opportunities to support your local community through paid community leave

WGEA certified work environment

Flexible working across most of our roles

A socially responsible work environment, on track to be carbon neutral by 2030

Great benefits to support your health and wellbeing, including access to discounted products

Mental health support for you and your family through our Sonder assistance program

Who are you?

Highly analytical who has worked within a PMO/ TO environment, ideally on a large-scale business and technology change

Financially astute, experienced in managing and tracking budgets and detailed forecasts. CA/CPA preferred but not essential

Great with stakeholders, a skilled communicator who can influence to achieve outcomes

Detail orientated, with a strong focus on accuracy, quality and governance.

Blackmores Group is a leading natural health company with proud Australian heritage, with extensive reach across Asia Pacific.  Founded by visionary naturopath Maurice Blackmore in 1932, our vision is to connect every person on earth to the healing power of nature by combining our knowledge of nature and science to deliver quality health solutions to people and their pets everywhere, every day.

Blackmores Group operates in over 13 markets, with headquarters and a state-of-the-art manufacturing facility in Australia, and offices across South East Asia and China.

Computershare has an exciting opportunity for a permanent full-time Senior CIRT Analyst to join our Computershare Shared Services (CSS) team within our Global Information Security (GIS) department.

A role you will love

As a Senior CIRT (Cyber Incident Response Team) Analyst, you will play a critical hands-on role within the Cyber Defence team, responsible for leading complex incident investigations, building and tuning threat detection capabilities, and mentoring SOC Analysts to support global 24/7 operations. In this role, you will act as the primary escalation point for incidents that exceed Tier 1/2 capabilities and ensures operational continuity outside of Security Operations leadership working hours. This includes close collaboration with teams like Security Engineering, Threat Intelligence, the NOC and Incident Management to manage and resolve cyber security incidents to competition.

Alongside our colleagues in Security Engineering, which drives strategic control implementation, you will be focused on the operational and tactical build out of threat detection and response. You will proactively translate real-world threats and attack behaviours into effective detection logic across SIEM and EDR platforms, conduct targeted threat hunts and help embed high-confidence detection into playbooks and response workflows, supporting our Incident Detection and Response Capability.

Our Senior CIRT Analysts are regionally aligned in a follow-the-sun model including positions in the Americas, EMEA and APAC. They have a global presence, but also regional expertise, working alongside and advising our regional CISO teams on regional compliance and reporting requirements from a technical perspective.



Other key responsibilities include:

Act as the senior escalation point for complex or high-severity incidents.
Lead incident response lifecycle from detection through to post-incident review.
Perform high level forensic analysis across cloud, endpoint and network data.
Develop and execute hypothesis driven hunts across available telemetry.
Use results to identify gaps or refine detection logic.
Build, tune, and document detection logic in Sentinel, Defender, CrowdStrike and other platforms.
Translate threat intelligence into rules and analytics to support incidents.
Maintain and execute MITRE ATT&CK coverage plans.
Design and improve operational playbooks and SOAR workflows.
Implement response logic for recurring incident types.
Support the development of SOC Analysts by providing escalation support, training and structured feedback.


What will you bring to the role?

Flexibility to work an on-call rotation which will include some weekends and public holidays (current schedule is 1 week every 6 weeks but is subject to change)
Proven experience in SOC, IR or similar roles with demonstrable in threat hunt or tier 3 response
Experience building detection logic and analytics rules (e.g. KQL, Sigma)
Deep understanding of MITRE ATT&CK, threat actors, and attack chains
Strong verbal and written communication skills including report writing skills, the ability to brief groups of people and the ability to translate technical terms into easy-to-understand concepts for non-technical colleagues
Experience in financial services, aviation, government or other regulated industries

Bonus points if you have:

GIAC certifications (e.g. GCIA, GCIH, GNFA, GMON, GCFA), Microsoft SC-200, AZ-500 or equivalent
Experience with Sentinel, Defender and CrowdStrike
Strong scripting knowledge (PowerShell, python etc)
Knowledge of Security Frameworks including SOC2, ISO 27001 and NIST
Active geopolitical awareness
Bachelor's degree or a master's degree in a relevant field

Our Company

At Ecocene, we believe that meaningful environmental change starts with passionate people who are committed to protecting and restoring our natural world.

We're a forward-thinking ecological services and technology company delivering measurable biodiversity and ecosystem restoration outcomes. Our mission is to empower organisations and communities with the expertise and intelligent solutions needed to protect and restore nature at scale.

About Ecocene Intelligence

Ecocene Intelligence is our cutting-edge data technology division that transforms complex ecological information into actionable insights through our flagship Ecoda platform. This cloud-based solution integrates remote sensing data and field observations using advanced analytics, streamlining biodiversity monitoring, compliance reporting, and environmental decision-making for projects of any scale. We're building Ecoda to democratise biodiversity monitoring and empower teams worldwide on their journey toward nature positive outcomes.

The Role

Ecocene Intelligence is seeking a Principal Remote Sensing Analyst to be part of its team, leading Ecocene Intelligence projects, developing new remote sensing products and overseeing the refinement of our remote sensing data processing pipeline. The Principal Remote Sensing Analyst will also train and mentor analysts and collaborate closely with Ecocene Expertise’s Earth Observation team.

About You

As part of the team, you’ll play a critical role in a rapidly growing, high-tech startup, solving real problems every day – and having fun while you’re at it. You will be well supported by other experts in remote sensing, specialists in various fields of environmental science and a team of analysts and field scientists.

You’ll be supervising the processing of a variety of remote sensing data to produce meaningful metrics which enable our customers to better manage their environment and report to government regulators.

You will provide technical leadership on remote sensing in the design and delivery of projects, undertake research and development in collaboration with peers and build skills and capacity within the team of remote sensing analysts and data scientists. 

You’re a collaborative team player and thrive on working closely with people from all levels of the business.

Your Skills

An undergraduate degree in a relevant scientific field that incorporates significant geospatial coursework or a relevant Bachelor’s degree with postgraduate qualification in geospatial science - examples of relevant degrees include (but are not limited to): geospatial science, environmental science, geography, data science

Deep expertise in remote sensing data processing and analysis

Well-developed leadership skills with an ability and willingness to train and mentor others

A focus on quality control and data assurance

Exceptional research, analysis and problem-solving skills

An ability to enthusiastically contribute, work effectively with people from all levels of business, and enjoy being part of a team

Excitement for helping people use data and technology to solve environmental issues

Why Join Ecocene?

When you join Ecocene Intelligence, you become part of a rapidly growing, high-tech startup at the forefront of environmental innovation. Every day brings meaningful challenges where you'll work with cutting-edge tools, from remote sensing and AI-driven analytics to sophisticated ecological monitoring systems, while making a tangible contribution to a more sustainable future.

You'll collaborate with a passionate, talented team that values both positive environmental outcomes and an engaging work culture. Together, we're not just building technology; we're creating solutions that help restore the planet.

Our Values

Ecocene empowers everyone to approach, own, and solve problems creatively. Our Values provide the foundation for the way in which we work, with all employees actively incorporating them into their everyday roles.

We pursue excellence – We’re passionate people committed to delivering outstanding results

We tackle the challenge together – We pitch in, support and encourage each other to deliver as a team

We adapt on demand – We’re responsive to change, and ready to pivot to put it at our advantage

We stay grounded – We keep it real, communicating openly, honestly and with trust

We operate with respect – We act with integrity, take accountability and treat people with respect

Ecocene is for everyone, so come as you are. Diversity makes our team more creative, fun, and effective, so bring your whole self to the application process, and we will too!

Benefits of Joining Ecocene

Professional development budget

Employee Assistance Program

Hybrid work arrangements

Fantastic culture and social events

Being part of building a natural future

Job description:



Join us and let's make a bigger difference together.

Established in 1840, we're Australia's first member owned wellbeing company. Today we have over $1 billion in revenue and provide smart solutions and services to more than 700,000 Australians. We employ over 7000 people, and our purpose is to Help People to Thrive.

It's an exciting time to be joining Australian Unity - we have grown significantly over recent years and are transforming to capitalise on further growth opportunities to help our customers and employees thrive. We operate with commercial principles and with a strong social purpose to create community value. Australian Unity is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

Our Opportunity

The Data Delivery Lead will play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering strategic data initiatives that drive measurable business value and support our enterprise transformation. Sitting within the Data team, you will lead an internal cross functional squad and oversee end-to-end delivery of key data projects, including migration, integration, and transformation, ensuring alignment with organisational priorities and outcomes.

This is a highly collaborative role, working closely with the Head of Data Strategy, Product Owners, business stakeholders, and other platform squads to deliver integrated solutions that enable strategic outcomes. You'll provide leadership to high performing delivery teams in a fast-paced environment optimising team operations, removing delivery blockers, and embedding continuous improvement practices to enhance productivity and ways of working to deliver business value.

To be successful in this role, you will leverage AU's hybrid agile and waterfall methodology, showcase strong leadership, facilitation, and problem-solving skills, with proven experience leading cross functional teams in large, complex enterprise environments. You'll be delivery focused, commercially aware, and passionate about enabling teams to deliver value iteratively and sustainably.

Accountabilities Include:

Manage the delivery of strategic data projects ensuring outcomes are delivered on time, within scope, and on budget, while delivering measurable business value
Lead a team of data engineers, testers and analysts to deliver strategic data initiatives, fostering a high-performance culture and embedding continuous improvement practices, ensuring alignment with business priorities and product roadmaps
Coordinate priorities, resolve delivery challenges, and manage dependencies across teams and platforms to achieve integrated enterprise outcomes
Drive delivery excellence by outlining data team deliverables, maintaining delivery health, and embedding agile and continuous improvement practices to enhance team flow and responsiveness
Proactively manage risks, issues, and dependencies across teams and project work, escalating critical items and ensuring governance standards are met
Provide transparent reporting on delivery status, risks, and performance metrics to leadership, ensuring visibility and alignment with program and portfolio objectives

About You

Proven experience (5+ years) leading the end-to-end delivery of data initiatives in large, complex enterprise environments, ideally within sectors such as financial services, health services, or other regulated industries
Day-to-day coordination on progress, prioritisation and problem solving with the data implementation team

Commercial acumen with experience in budget management, resource planning, and vendor engagement.
Tertiary qualifications in IT, Business, Data, or a related field from a recognised institution

Hello. We’re Virgin Australia.

We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way.

We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

What you’ll be doing

We’re looking for an Ancillary Product & Strategy Specialist to help us grow the products our guests love. This role sits within our Revenue Management team and reports to the Senior Manager, Ancillary Product & Strategy. You’ll be part of a team that’s shaping the future of our product portfolio – from strategy and performance reporting to proposition evolution and BAU product management.

You’ll work across the business to support the development of our 3-year product strategy and roadmap, dive deep into data to uncover insights, and help bring new ideas to life. You’ll also get to see the impact of your work every time you fly with us – because what you do will help make our guests’ experience even better.

You’ll be great in this role if you…

You’re a strategic thinker with a knack for turning data into stories that drive decisions. You’ve got experience in strategy, consulting or commercial analytics, and you’re comfortable working with ambiguity. You know your way around Excel and PowerBI, and you’re confident communicating with stakeholders at all levels.

You’re curious, collaborative, and love solving problems. You’re not afraid to challenge the status quo and bring fresh ideas to the table. And you care about doing things the right way – with integrity, attention to detail, and a focus on impact.

To be considered, you’ll need:

A relevant Bachelor’s degree
2+ years’ experience in strategy/management consulting or similar commercial analytics roles
Strong skills in data analysis, insight generation, and stakeholder communication
Advanced Excel and PowerBI (or similar tools)

What you’ll get from us

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year)
A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs
One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road
Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide
Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services
Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health
‘Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you.

When everyone is included, everyone wins

We’re all individuals. And we love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.
